      <h2 style="text-align:center;">Is a Power Flush Right for Your Wirral Property?</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">We give an honest assessment before every job. Power flushing is excellent but it is not right for every Wirral system.</p>

      <p style="font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);margin-bottom:0.75rem;text-align:center;">Power flushing IS right for your Wirral property if</p>
      <div class="pf-who-grid" style="margin-top:0;">
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Your system is more than 5 years old and shows signs of contamination</strong><p>Cold spots, slow warm-up, noisy boiler or radiators barely heating. A power flush resolves these in the majority of Wirral cases.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>You have a sealed modern system with 15mm or 22mm pipework</strong><p>Standard sealed systems in Wirral properties built after 1995 are ideal candidates. Straightforward, effective and low risk with our own Gas Safe engineers.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>You have a 1975-1995 estate property with microbore pipework</strong><p>Yes, but we must use our specialist microbore technique with chemical pre-treatment. Tell us your property type when you call and we will confirm the approach and any price variation.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>You are installing a new boiler on your existing Wirral system</strong><p>All major manufacturers require a clean system as a warranty condition. A written power flush report from us is your evidence of compliance before the new boiler is connected.</p></div></div>
      </div>

      <p style="font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);margin:1.5rem 0 0.75rem;text-align:center;">Power flushing may NOT be right if</p>
      <div class="pf-who-grid" style="margin-top:0;">
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-no"><span class="pf-who-icon">!</span><div><strong>Your Wirral Victorian terrace has an open-vented gravity-fed system</strong><p>Some older Birkenhead and Wallasey properties still have gravity-fed systems. These require different technique than a modern sealed system. Tell us your system type when you call.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-no"><span class="pf-who-icon">!</span><div><strong>Your system has very old heavily corroded pipework</strong><p>Extremely old systems with severely corroded pipework carry a higher risk of exposing leaks. Sometimes a chemical flush or targeted radiator replacement is more appropriate. We assess at no cost.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-no"><span class="pf-who-icon">!</span><div><strong>Your boiler keeps losing pressure</strong><p>Pressure loss means you have a leak somewhere in the system. Power flushing does not seal leaks. The leak must be identified and repaired first. We diagnose this before recommending any flush.</p></div></div>
