  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f8fafc;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">What Happens During a Wirral Power Flush</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">A step-by-step breakdown of exactly what our engineers do on every Wirral job.</p>
      <div class="pf-steps" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-step"><div class="pf-step-num">1</div><div><strong>System assessment, 20 to 30 minutes</strong><p>We inspect the system, identify the pipe type, check for microbore connections, test a water sample and assess contamination level. Any concerns are discussed before starting. If we believe a power flush is not right for your system, we say so.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-step"><div class="pf-step-num">2</div><div><strong>Chemical treatment added and system run</strong><p>For standard systems, a professional-strength cleaning chemical is introduced. For microbore systems, a dedicated dispersant is added first and allowed to work for several hours before the machine is connected. This step is not optional on microbore.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-step"><div class="pf-step-num">3</div><div><strong>Power flush machine connected</strong><p>The machine is connected at the pump head or at a radiator tail. For microbore, lower velocity settings are used throughout to avoid junction blocking.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-step"><div class="pf-step-num">4</div><div><strong>Full system flushed in both directions</strong><p>Water pumped through the entire system in both directions. Each radiator isolated and flushed individually. Microbore legs flushed one at a time. Contaminated water passes through the machine filter and is captured.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-step"><div class="pf-step-num">5</div><div><strong>Neutraliser added. Inhibitor dosed. System balanced.</strong><p>Neutraliser added and pH confirmed. System refilled with clean water and full-strength inhibitor dosed to BS 7593 standard. Every radiator balanced. System pressure set. Full heating cycle confirmed.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-step"><div class="pf-step-num">6</div><div><strong>Written report issued same day</strong><p>Written report covering the date, contamination level found, chemicals used, inhibitor dose and final system condition. This is your warranty evidence document if your manufacturer requires proof of system cleaning before a new boiler is installed.</p></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


