  <!-- LIMITATIONS AND ALTERNATIVES -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f8fafc;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">What Power Flushing Cannot Fix</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">We give Wirral homeowners honest information before every job.</p>
      <div class="pf-limitations" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-limit"><span class="pf-limit-x">✕</span><div><strong>It will not fix a boiler that keeps losing pressure</strong><p>Pressure loss on a Wirral system means a leak somewhere in the circuit. Power flushing does not seal leaks. The leak must be identified and repaired first.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-limit"><span class="pf-limit-x">✕</span><div><strong>It will not fix broken or seized valve bodies</strong><p>If a TRV is mechanically broken rather than sludged, it needs replacing. We identify and can replace faulty valves on the same visit as the flush.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-limit"><span class="pf-limit-x">✕</span><div><strong>It will not fix mechanical boiler faults</strong><p>A power flush cleans the water circuit. It cannot repair a failed pump, faulty PCB or broken igniter. Mechanical faults need a repair, not a flush.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-limit"><span class="pf-limit-x">✕</span><div><strong>It is not a permanent solution</strong><p>Sludge and magnetite will build up again over time. Annual inhibitor checks and a magnetic filter slow the process. We recommend a power flush every 5 to 7 years on a well-maintained Wirral system.</p></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">Power Flushing Wirral. Your Questions Answered</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Straight answers to what Wirral homeowners ask most before booking.</p>
      <div class="pf-faq">
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">COST</span>&nbsp; How much does power flushing cost on the Wirral?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A power flush on the Wirral costs £350 for up to 10 radiators and £450 for 11 to 15 radiators. Both prices include all cleaning chemicals, full inhibitor dose to BS 7593 and a written system report. Microbore systems require additional time but are quoted at the same fixed prices. No hidden extras on any Wirral job.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">MICROBORE</span>&nbsp; My Wirral estate property has microbore pipes. Can you still power flush?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes, but with specialist technique. Microbore systems require a dedicated chemical dispersant to break sludge down before the machine is connected, lower velocity settings throughout and individual flushing of each microbore leg. This prevents junction blockages that can make the system worse. We carry the correct equipment and chemicals for microbore on every Wirral van. Tell us your system type when you call and we will confirm the approach.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">NEW BOILER</span>&nbsp; Do I need a power flush before my new Wirral boiler is installed?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>In most cases yes. Worcester Bosch, Vaillant, Ideal and Baxi all require a clean system as a warranty condition. A written power flush report is your evidence that the requirement was met before the new boiler was connected. Without it, a manufacturer can reject a warranty claim on the grounds that the system was contaminated. We carry out power flushes as part of new boiler installations across all Wirral CH postcodes.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">HOW LONG</span>&nbsp; How long does a power flush take on the Wirral?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A standard sealed system in a 3-bed Wirral property takes 5 to 7 hours. Microbore systems take 7 to 9 hours due to the additional chemical pre-treatment step. Large south Wirral properties with 13 or more radiators take a full day. We always recommend a morning start and complete in a single visit. Someone must be present throughout.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">LEAKS</span>&nbsp; Can power flushing cause leaks in my Wirral system?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A correctly carried out power flush at low pressure does not cause leaks in structurally sound pipework. It can expose pre-existing pinhole leaks in heavily corroded radiators that were previously sealed by debris. When this happens we identify the faulty radiator and can replace it on the same visit. We always carry out a system assessment before starting to identify any radiators at high risk.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-green">GAS SAFE</span>&nbsp; Are you Gas Safe registered for Wirral power flushing?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. All power flushing across the Wirral is carried out by our own directly employed Gas Safe registered engineers. Verify at <a href="https://www.gassaferegister.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">gassaferegister.co.uk</a>. We never use sub-contractors.</p></div></details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


